Scope note (not part of the MIT grant above):

- The MIT license applies to the SOURCE CODE in this repository ONLY. It does
  NOT cover any trained model weights or training data.

- TRAINED MODEL WEIGHTS are NOT licensed under the MIT license above — neither
  the large models (e.g. v3-37M and the others under model/, which are
  gitignored and not distributed here) nor the small browser model that IS
  committed to this repository.

  The browser model weights — the Model Capsule under viz/public/weights/ (the
  ~116k-parameter distilled net the web app runs) — are committed and deployed
  to GitHub Pages for ONE purpose: so that the web player and visualization can
  let people see and play the model in order to illustrate how its architecture
  works. With respect to those weights:

    * They are provided for PERSONAL, NON-COMMERCIAL use only.
    * They are made available STRICTLY for that illustrative purpose (viewing
      and playing the model within this web tool). No right is granted to
      redistribute, sublicense, sell, or reuse the weights in other software,
      products, or services, or for any commercial purpose.
    * They are derived in part from TWIC (theweekinchess.com) data, whose terms
      are "personal use only" — which independently prohibits commercial use and
      wholesale redistribution of the data and anything derived from it.

  No warranty is given for the weights, and all rights not expressly granted are
  reserved.

- TRAINING DATA (the corpus and shards under data/) is NOT covered by this
  license, is not distributed here (gitignored), and — being derived in part
  from TWIC "personal use only" data — is personal-use only and must not be
  redistributed wholesale.

- Third-party assets bundled with the web tool retain their own licenses; see
  viz/THIRD_PARTY.md for attribution.

See the README "Provenance and license" section.
